text: Hey Kevin, thanks for reporting. Since you did post this yesterday, I want to check have you already been helped by another HubSpotter?

Hey there <@U02E6LPLW72> I’ve updated that marketplace listing doc to include a link to another doc that defines what is meant by active unique installs.

The definition can be found here:
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/app-marketplace-listing-requirements#:~:text=active%2C%20unique%20installs>
> Active installs are the number of unique HubSpot production accounts showing recent successful activity.
In other words no test accounts do not count.
<@U7SL518D6> No. Not yet. Just got a standard support response saying someone is looking into this but no real update over the last day or so.

Can you send me the ticket id from support?

<https://app.HubSpot.com/l/support-inbox/>
This should take you to your support inbox, the ticket id will be in the URL when you click on the ticket (might also show in the ticket itself)
